"```sql\nSELECT \n    (SELECT SUM(ViewCount) FROM posts \n     JOIN users ON posts.OwnerUserId = users.Id \n     WHERE users.DisplayName = 'Mornington') \n    - \n    (SELECT SUM(ViewCount) FROM posts \n     JOIN users ON posts.OwnerUserId = users.Id \n     WHERE users.DisplayName = 'Amos') \n    AS ViewCountDifference;\n```\nThis SQL query calculates the difference in the total view count of posts made by users with the display names 'Mornington' and 'Amos'. It uses subqueries to sum the view counts for each user and then subtracts the two sums to find the difference."